What you need to know:  It was a game of two halves as Kabras Sugar rallied from behind 18-8 at the break to beat Menengai Oilers 34-28 in a nerve-racking final at the Bullring, Kakamega on Saturday.Kabras touched down three tries, two conversions and five penalties to recapture the title they won last in 2016 when they beat Impala Saracens in the final.